title: Identify the input values
text: When considering percent grade as a function, the input values are grade-point averages, so the domain is {0.0, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 2.5, 3.0, 3.5, 4.0}.

title: Identify the output values
text: When considering percent grade as a function, the output values are percent grades, so the range is the set of all integers between 0 and 100 .

title: Classify the relation
text: Because the input value 0.0 leads to 56 different output values, percent grade is not a function of the grade-point average.
